# Commands

Run from repo root. Node **>= 24.14.0**. Package manager: **npm**.

## Before claiming done (CI order)

1. `npm run format:check` — or `npm run format` then re-check
2. `npm run lint`
3. `npm run typecheck`
4. `npm test -- --ci`

**Dependency / Dependabot work:** also `npm run doctor` after `npm ci` (same check runs in Test Check CI). If doctor reports SDK patch drift, `npx expo install --fix`.

Report what ran and the outcome. If a step was skipped, say why.

## Development

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `npm install` | Install deps |
| `npm start` | Metro bundler |
| `npm run android` | Run on Android emulator/device |
| `npm run format` | Fix Prettier (broader than `format:check`) |
| `npm run typecheck` | TypeScript check (`tsc --noEmit`) |
| `npm run doctor` | Expo SDK / native-module alignment (`expo-doctor`) |

## CI mirrors

- Lint + format: `.github/workflows/lint.yml`
- Test: `.github/workflows/test.yml`
- TypeScript + Expo health: `.github/workflows/quality-gates.yml` (`typecheck`, `expo-doctor`, `expo install --check`)
- Release on tag: `.github/workflows/eas-build.yml` + `.eas/workflows/create-production-builds.yml`
- PR preview (native compile on demand): `.github/workflows/preview-build.yml` (label `preview-build`)

## PR workflow

Slash commands in `.cursor/commands/`: `/create-pr-branch`, `/generate-pr-description`, `/create-pr`, `/onboard`, `/dep-bump`, `/handle-dependabot`. Align with team PR title format: `[#NNN]: Description` (Project 4 Fluent Mobile Board — [docs/issue-tracking.md](../../docs/issue-tracking.md)). CI map: [docs/ci.md](../../docs/ci.md).

## Do not run without user request

- **Push to `main`** or commit agent work on `main` — always use a ticketed feature branch + PR ([delivery.mdc](./delivery.mdc))
- Force push, hard reset
- Commits or push to feature branches (unless user asks)
- Modifying `.env` or secrets

## Expo / CNG (Android-only)

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `npm run prebuild` | Regenerate `android/` from `app.config.ts` (`--platform android`) |
| `npx eas build --profile development --platform android` | EAS dev-client APK (requires `EXPO_TOKEN` + project access) |
| `git tag v1.0.0 && git push origin v1.0.0` | Production Android release (see `.eas/README.md`) |

If `MainApplication does not exist`, `rm -rf android` then `npm run prebuild`. Regenerate bootsplash with `--platforms=android` only (see README).

See [`.cursor/rules/android-only.mdc`](./android-only.mdc) and [`.cursor/rules/expo-mcp.mdc`](./expo-mcp.mdc) — authenticate Expo MCP before SDK/EAS work.
